ICE to capture and search for information included in applications for court orders authorizing ICE to
intercept oral, wire, or electronic communications, such as telephone conversations and emails. 
When ICE is engaged in joint investigations with state or municipal law enforcement agencies, ICE agents may also support requests filed with state courts for electronic surveillance under the applicable state’s electronic surveillance laws. These requests will be captured in ELSUR as well.
